&lt;p&gt;Zocdoc’s most important asset is our people. As a Senior Manager of Business Development, you’ll be responsible for creating, managing, and growing strategic partnerships critical to Zocdoc’s growth. This role will initiate and negotiate new partnerships, grow and develop ongoing partner relationships, and manage partner performance with an initial focus on strategic distribution partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has a proven track record of successfully managing partnerships with large companies, driving measurable growth through external relationships, and thinking strategically about complex business issues. This person should be comfortable owning both new business development and existing partner performance, including identifying opportunities to improve results, expand relationships, and create mutual value for Zocdoc and our partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be responsible for coordinating cross-functional partnerships in collaboration with various teams across the organization, including product, engineering, marketing, operations, finance, legal, analytics, sales, and leadership. This role will report to the Sr. Director of Business Development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll enjoy this role if you are...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personally motivated by owning a project or relationship from start to finish. You will manage the entire partner lifecycle from ideation to execution, including partner performance, growth, and long-term relationship management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced at building a network, both internal and external to your organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about finding creative, scalable, and mutually beneficial partner opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercially and analytically minded. You enjoy understanding what is driving performance, identifying opportunities for improvement, and translating insights into action&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong relationship builder and negotiator. You enjoy finding financially and commercially beneficial terms for new and existing partner agreements&lt;/li&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Healthcare should work for patients, but it doesn’t. In their time of need, they call down outdated insurance directories. Then wait on hold. Then wait weeks for the privilege of a visit. Then wait in a room solely designed for waiting. Then wait for a surprise bill. In any other consumer industry, the companies delivering such a poor customer experience would not survive. But in healthcare, patients lack market power. Which means they are expected to accept the unacceptable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Zocdoc’s mission is to give power to the patient. To do that, we’ve built the leading healthcare marketplace that makes it easy to find and book in-person or virtual care in all 50 states, across +200 specialties and +12k insurance plans. By giving patients the ability to see and choose, we give them power. In doing so, we can make healthcare work like every other consumer sector, where businesses compete for customers, not the other way around. In time, this will drive quality up and prices down.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re 18 years old and the leader in our space, but we are still just getting started. If you like solving important, complex problems alongside deeply thoughtful, driven, and collaborative teammates, read on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact on our Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is central to shaping how patients and providers perceive and engage with Zocdoc. You’ll help ensure our brand reflects the humanity of healthcare and the value of Zocdoc through storytelling, creative, and community engagement that strengthen our reputation and drive affinity. Your work will make Zocdoc not just a platform people use, but a brand they love, believe in and want to be a part of.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day to day is…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Zocdoc’s organic social strategy (Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, and emerging channels), building awareness, affinity, and engagement among patients and providers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute always-on social programming and campaigns, ensuring content is high-quality, on-brand, and optimized for each platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead content ideation and oversee production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage internal and external creatives to deliver best-in-class social content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to broader brand initiatives, bringing social insight and creative input into the development of strategy and creative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experiment with formats, trends and real-time moments that extend reach and cultural relevance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead community management, acting as the voice of Zocdoc on social platforms, participating in conversations, and building meaningful relationships with audiences and creators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own performance tracking and analytics for organic social, translating insights into clear actions and continuous optimization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build systems and workflows that enable efficient, high-quality creative production at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional alignment. Partner with internal stakeholders to ensure integrated storytelling and maximize the impact of campaigns, launches, and brand moments across social channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive Zocdoc’s creator strategy, ensuring strong brand alignment, and measurable impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
